text: <@U010BJ06WTE>Out of the three the only one i would consider is ene legna however how about Tena yestilign it’s a greeting we use and we can play off the traditional use of it as tenayestelgn doesn’t involve touching when you say hi. Traditionally we bow our head from a distance and keep it moving. In addition it has the word Tena and yestilign separately both words separately give us more room to work with it in relation to branding. In addition since it is a catchy phrase embedded in our culture we can use it in many settings.
